<0xC5><0xA0>imon Ornest: We want to gather positive energy at our concerts
What do you think is going to happen in less than a month?
This is one of those disaster reports that we people like to jump on.
With our band The Tap Tap, we’re more likely to make fun of it and say that we’re the only band in the world that can collect enough positive energy to stop or prevent the end of the world.
In December, you will also realize a unique project with three concerts against the end of the world.
Can you introduce the project to our readers?
This is a nationwide benefit event that we have been planning for two years.
For this, we want to use the marketing potential of the Mayan calendar, the end of which is predicted for December 21 at 11:10 am.
The day before, i.e. 20 December, three concerts will take place simultaneously in Prague, Brno and Ostrava from 21:00.
The end of the concerts is supposed to be around the time when the Mayan calendar ends on the Pacific island of Kiribati, which is located in a time zone about 12 hours ahead of us.
Where did this idea come from?
Initially probably from me, then we designed the idea together with our graphic designer Honza Augusta.
Not only do we want to collect enough positive energy to prevent the end of the world, but we also want to think together with the public about the state in which we once give this world to our children.
On the occasion of the end of the Mayan calendar, we have also developed a unique collection of shoes, T-shirts, bags and keychains against the end of the world, with the purchase of which people can also support us through www.e-tap.cz.
The band The Tap Tap, together with other performers, has also recorded the so-called anthem against the end of the world entitled "The end of the world falls out".
Already today, the anthem is very popular on YouTube. Will it also be heard at the benefit concerts?
Of course, and to the very end, provided that everything works out and the world does not end...
The anthem is to be sung by all the performers at all three concerts at the same time.
In addition, the anthems are broadcast live on Czech TV.
The text of the hymn comes from Tom<0xC3><0xA1><0xC5><0xA1> Han<0xC3><0xA1>k, who also plays the main character of Jesus in the video clip, also sings Xindl X with...
How did you come to work with both?
We also cooperate with other personalities of the Czech cultural scene, which is related to the fact that we realize many benefit events and concerts...
We strive to involve these people intensively in our projects.
It has been shown that most people are interested in working with us and enjoying it.
What purpose will the proceeds of the concerts benefit against the end of the world?
For the establishment of the accessible education center Studeo, where we have been working for six years together with the Tap Association at the Jedli<0xC4><0x8D>ka Institute.
The students of the Jedli<0xC4><0x8D>ka Institute are regularly supervised by lecturers who help them with various leisure activities.
Since the students themselves do not have the means to visit the lecturers, we want to help them in this way.
As part of the completion of the Jedli<0xC4><0x8D>ka Institute, we will create our own building, which we will then move into with this project.
Several groups and performers perform at each concert.
By what criteria did you choose them?
We wanted to create a program that appeals to all generations, including children.
In Prague, for example, Chinaski, Support Lesbians, Illustratosphere with Dan B<0xC3><0xA1>rta, The Tap Tap, Mari<0xC3><0xA1>n Bango and Ji<0xC5><0x99><0xC3><0xAD> Such<0xC3><0xBD> appear.
