What are the main sexually transmitted diseases?
Bacterial STIs include syphilis, chlamydia and tripper (gonorrhoea).
Common viral STIs are HIV, human papillomaviruses, genital herpes, or hepatitis.
Fillets and scabs are part of the parasitic STI.
Who are the main stakeholders?
