An ethnic abbreviation - just like my friends in Boston call themselves "Iren" or my friends in New York "Italian".
Later, I chose "Mexican-American".
But this was Mexico.
And in my grandfather’s home there was no need for abbreviations or hyphens.
I was just an American.
I speak Spanish, at least well enough to assert myself in that language at both ends of an interview.
